    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>Decmbr 17th</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revrd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Many thanks to you for<lb/> your long expected letter, which should
                not<lb/> have remained unanswered so long, had I have known<lb/> where to write to
                you, but your kind nature has made<lb/> allowances for my past neglect, so I avail
                myself<lb/> of the earliest opportunity, it is true had I have had<lb/> sufficient
                sense, might have heard from cousin<lb/>
                <persName>Myrtilla</persName> your direction still I flatter myself at<lb/> this
                late day a few lines from me will not prove<lb/> unacceptable, I am happy to hear
                you are well &amp; having<lb/> a pleasant time, &amp; making so many new
                friends<lb/> trust you will soon return to <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>, I
                am<lb/> quite selfish but since you have left I have made<lb/> another mine, &amp;
                am at housekeeping in <placeName>Arch Street</placeName><lb/> where I hope to have
                your pleasant company very often,</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I need not tell you how much I miss you, you know<lb/> we never know the value of
                friends until we loose them,<lb/> there has nothing transpired of any moment
                since<lb/> you left; the weather is very unhealthy, mild, &amp;<lb/> very damp,
                which certainly at this time of the<lb/> year is very <del>unhealthy</del>
                unseasonable. <persName>Mr Cohen</persName> has charge<lb/> of a stick which was
                sent from <placeName>Jerusalem</placeName><lb/> for you, picked by some sister from
                the<lb/> Lemon-branches of <persName>Rabbi Levy's</persName> garden,
                <add>?</add><lb/> sends her love &amp; misses you very much <persName>Sarah<lb/>
                    Nathan</persName> has gone before, she had a very<lb/> pleasant visit, I hear
                nothing new from<lb/>
                <placeName>New-York</placeName>, my husband &amp; <add>?</add> continue<lb/> very
                well, <persName>Chary</persName> sends you her love, &amp; a Miss.<lb/> your books
                    <persName>Ellen</persName> says have been taken out<lb/> of the Custom-house
                &amp; the duty paid on them,<lb/>
                <persName>Esther</persName>, <persName>Jacob-Lion</persName>,
                    <persName>Chary</persName>
                <persName>Isabella</persName> beg me to<lb/> remember them to you,
                    <persName>Davids</persName> best regards<lb/> to you, that this scrawl may find
                you<lb/> in the enjoyment of health, &amp; happiness,<lb/> you need no words to
                assure you of the<lb/> sincerity of your true friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName role="author">Elvira Solis</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
